<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="334" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.77/69.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>If the Department wishes to object to the Nuevitas-Caibarién railway
                            matter the Legation should be instructed at once as the project is now
                            under discussion in Congress.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
